12:49.960 --> 12:54.875
Somebody told me to believe

12:57.830 --> 13:02.608
To believe

13:12.620 --> 13:13.996
Car's loaded.
You ready to head out?

13:15.670 --> 13:17.035
Cabin's the safest place,

13:17.040 --> 13:18.701
and there are no cameras.

13:18.710 --> 13:19.995
-Where's Levi?
-[soft grunt]

13:20.000 --> 13:23.743
I could not find Levi,
so I bring him.

13:25.040 --> 13:26.826
-[sniffs]
-[hisses]

13:30.750 --> 13:31.990
He is new.

13:35.960 --> 13:37.666
From your colony?

13:37.670 --> 13:38.705
[Ryn] Yes.

13:38.710 --> 13:41.611
And he must be hungry.

13:41.620 --> 13:43.611
Come with me. I'll
get you some breakfast.

13:45.790 --> 13:48.611
Hey, Ryn,
before you do this,

13:48.620 --> 13:49.700
we have some questions.

13:50.830 --> 13:52.821
If you mate in human form,

13:52.830 --> 13:54.912
will the baby
be born as a human?

13:54.920 --> 13:57.662
Should it be born
on land or at sea?

13:57.670 --> 14:00.787
The only documented story
of a birth on land

14:00.790 --> 14:04.783
by a member of your colony
is the Charles Pownall story.

14:05.920 --> 14:07.615
And the baby lived.

14:07.620 --> 14:09.918
Yes, but
with great difficulty.

14:09.920 --> 14:12.957
We're not sure
what'll happen, exactly,

14:12.960 --> 14:14.780
if you get pregnant
this way.

14:14.790 --> 14:18.669
Whatever this baby is,
it will be family.

14:28.080 --> 14:30.878
Hey, Ryn, you, uh...

14:30.880 --> 14:33.667
You asked to borrow
my cell yesterday.

14:36.120 --> 14:37.747
I thought you should
have your own.

14:38.920 --> 14:40.911
[Maddie]
Ryn, isn't that nice?

14:48.880 --> 14:51.075
[somber music]

14:53.880 --> 14:55.074
[paper crinkles]

15:16.710 --> 15:18.996
[dramatic music]

15:30.040 --> 15:32.167
[rock music playing
in The Anchor]

15:35.120 --> 15:36.917
[hissing]

15:36.920 --> 15:39.036
[loud conversations
and laughter]

15:42.750 --> 15:44.069
-[hisses]
-[soft hiss]

15:44.080 --> 15:46.036
I got the goods
to get it done

15:46.040 --> 15:47.996
Yeah, I got the goods
to get it done

15:48.000 --> 15:49.820
I'll get it done,
I'll get it done

15:53.540 --> 15:56.168
Your grandmother wrote
that letter to my mother.

15:57.580 --> 15:58.956
"I'm not my husband.

15:58.960 --> 16:00.996
I do not_contro|
hIS actions."

16:02.170 --> 16:03.785
What do you think it means?

16:03.790 --> 16:07.374
She was apologizing

16:07.380 --> 16:09.416
for something
your grandfather did,

16:09.420 --> 16:10.785
apparently
something horriﬁc.

16:10.790 --> 16:13.782
You're suggesting he had
something to do with the fire?

16:13.790 --> 16:16.532
She's making amends, Ted.

16:16.540 --> 16:18.417
I never knew my Grandpa Caleb.

16:18.420 --> 16:19.569
They said
he was eccentric.

16:19.580 --> 16:21.571
He'd drink too much,
lose his temper.

16:25.710 --> 16:27.530
I need
to show you something.

16:29.880 --> 16:33.532
[rock music playing]

16:34.670 --> 16:35.705
[hisses]

16:35.710 --> 16:36.870
[pool balls clack]

16:36.880 --> 16:38.700
[both hissing]

16:38.710 --> 16:39.916
Levi.

16:39.920 --> 16:42.491
Levi who?
I don't know a Levi.

16:54.790 --> 16:57.532
[fire crackling]

17:03.830 --> 17:06.663
I'm not my family, okay?

17:08.540 --> 17:09.825
I need you to know that.

17:09.830 --> 17:11.707
This man in your family.

17:13.500 --> 17:14.569
Charles.

17:16.750 --> 17:19.913
He loved one like me,

17:19.920 --> 17:21.706
and his love turned bad.

17:21.710 --> 17:23.951
It makes him angry.

17:23.960 --> 17:25.916
He killed my people.

17:25.920 --> 17:27.876
And it starts with love.

17:29.790 --> 17:30.779
Like...

17:32.620 --> 17:33.871
[crying]
Like Ben love Ryn.

17:33.880 --> 17:35.916
It's not gonna
happen like that.

17:37.540 --> 17:38.609
I won't let it.

17:38.620 --> 17:40.702
Then why do you lie?

17:40.710 --> 17:42.496
Not tell me
all this time?

17:43.790 --> 17:44.950
You say nothing.

17:44.960 --> 17:46.746
I didn't know
what to say.

17:46.750 --> 17:47.739
No!

17:49.710 --> 17:50.825
I do not trust.

18:00.750 --> 18:01.785
[door unlatches]

18:08.620 --> 18:09.780
It didn't go well?

18:10.960 --> 18:11.949
I'll talk to her.

18:12.960 --> 18:14.530
[sighs]

18:28.710 --> 18:29.779
Ben.

18:32.040 --> 18:33.576
Yeah.

18:35.880 --> 18:36.915
Ryn.

18:38.670 --> 18:39.739
Maddie.

18:41.750 --> 18:43.570
You're a fast learner.

18:52.750 --> 18:53.819
Ryn?

18:55.620 --> 18:57.747
Yes. Ryn.

19:05.040 --> 19:06.871
Be good to her.

19:12.040 --> 19:14.668
Whoa.

19:14.670 --> 19:15.819
Oh, man.

19:18.670 --> 19:19.785
Holy!

19:19.790 --> 19:21.701
[laughs]

19:21.710 --> 19:22.745
Hi.

19:24.080 --> 19:26.662
In the dude's room. Okay.

19:26.670 --> 19:27.819
[sniffing]

19:29.040 --> 19:31.747
That makeup's banger.

19:31.750 --> 19:33.661
-[sniffing]
-[laughing]

19:33.670 --> 19:34.819
Damn. That tickles.

19:36.000 --> 19:38.662
-Huh.
-[sniffs, hisses]

19:38.670 --> 19:41.070
-[hisses]
-Okay, hold up a second.

19:41.080 --> 19:44.664
No. Not from water.

19:46.710 --> 19:47.745
[man groans]

19:47.750 --> 19:49.069
Aw, hell no.

19:49.080 --> 19:51.116
No. No no no no no.

19:51.120 --> 19:54.704
How many times do I have
to get rid of you freaks?

19:54.710 --> 19:56.666
-Come.
-[hisses]

19:56.670 --> 19:58.661
-[hisses]
-Who the hell is she?

19:58.670 --> 19:59.819
She is hunter.

19:59.830 --> 20:01.707
Hunter, okay.

20:01.710 --> 20:02.950
This way.
This way out. Go. Go.

20:05.120 --> 20:07.202
I found these a few days ago.

20:07.210 --> 20:09.030
They're from your mother
to my grandmother.

20:14.120 --> 20:16.168
My mother
wrote all of these?

20:17.420 --> 20:19.320
They had
a lot to write about.

20:21.080 --> 20:23.412
Yeah, mostly about
my crazy grandfather.

20:23.420 --> 20:26.457
There's crazy running
all up and down the bloodline.

20:28.250 --> 20:29.490
Sometimes I worry about Ben.

20:34.460 --> 20:37.111
He's just
a young man, Ted,

20:37.120 --> 20:39.327
trying to solve
all the problems
of the world.

20:40.460 --> 20:41.415
Oh, take them.

20:41.420 --> 20:43.490
Read them.

20:43.500 --> 20:46.412
They obviously meant
something to my grandmother.

20:46.420 --> 20:49.071
Hopefully, they'll mean
something to you.

20:52.080 --> 20:56.164
[soft music]

20:56.170 --> 20:57.159
Are you okay?

20:58.500 --> 21:00.206
Confused.

21:00.210 --> 21:01.416
He is different than us.

21:02.500 --> 21:04.286
The best way
to have sex on land

21:04.290 --> 21:06.167
is just
to let it feel good.

21:07.540 --> 21:09.326
Like with us.

21:09.330 --> 21:13.118
Remember when we were
first together,

21:13.120 --> 21:14.246
how we showed you?

21:16.120 --> 21:17.246
Now you show him.

21:20.210 --> 21:22.246
[door unlatches]

21:36.290 --> 21:37.450
It is time.

21:40.330 --> 21:43.117
Okay. I'll be outside.

21:49.500 --> 21:52.378
[inhales]

21:53.500 --> 21:55.240
[hisses]

21:55.250 --> 21:56.490
[dramatic music]

21:56.500 --> 21:57.615
[groaning]

22:00.210 --> 22:02.201
[crashes inside]

22:07.380 --> 22:10.167
[ominous music]

22:10.170 --> 22:11.535
-Wait.
-It could be dangerous, Maddie!

22:11.540 --> 22:13.371
We know they get violent
when they mate!

22:13.380 --> 22:15.245
Yeah, Ryn will know
what to do.

22:15.250 --> 22:16.569
We don't know him!

22:17.620 --> 22:18.609
He could hurt her!

22:19.620 --> 22:20.609
[grunting]

22:22.500 --> 22:24.377
[soft hiss]

22:24.380 --> 22:27.326
[Ryn panting]

22:30.250 --> 22:32.161
I don't like it,
either, okay,

22:32.170 --> 22:33.410
her being someone else.

22:33.420 --> 22:35.240
But we have to put
our feelings aside.

22:37.210 --> 22:38.370
You can do that?

22:41.290 --> 22:42.416
Listen.

22:42.420 --> 22:45.378
[silence]

22:47.620 --> 22:50.453
I told her to show him
how we do it.

22:50.460 --> 22:54.373
["Let Go" by Talos playing]

22:54.380 --> 22:58.453
The warnings lined

22:58.460 --> 23:00.610
The edges between us

23:02.210 --> 23:04.280
We were holdin' out

23:05.290 --> 23:06.666
Different on land.

23:09.290 --> 23:13.283
Escape in time

23:13.290 --> 23:15.531
To play down
what leaves us

23:15.540 --> 23:16.609
Like this.

23:16.620 --> 23:20.499
We were holdin' out

23:22.380 --> 23:25.702
No hiding
what seized us

23:25.710 --> 23:28.417
In the climb,
I was there for the deep

23:28.420 --> 23:30.456
Thought you'd see
and let go

23:30.460 --> 23:33.281
No hiding
what seized us

23:33.290 --> 23:35.576
Now your desert
was comforting me

23:35.580 --> 23:38.242
But the burn wanted more

23:38.250 --> 23:40.536
No hiding
what seized us

23:40.540 --> 23:42.451
When you clawed into me

23:42.460 --> 23:44.701
Did you see
that the wild was the road?

23:44.710 --> 23:48.453
No hiding
what seized us

23:48.460 --> 23:50.246
Fall into me

23:50.250 --> 23:53.708
Let the fires
just reach and let go

23:53.710 --> 23:56.326
Good. To Ryn.

23:58.710 --> 24:00.701
Yes.

24:00.710 --> 24:04.532
Why'd you lie
in the carnage with me?

24:04.540 --> 24:07.532
Why'd you gift me
your fallout?

24:07.540 --> 24:11.749
You were right,
it was on us to see

24:11.750 --> 24:14.708
We were holding out

24:14.710 --> 24:17.452
No hiding
what seized us

24:17.460 --> 24:20.372
In the climb,
I was there for the deep

24:20.380 --> 24:22.746
Thought you'd see
and let go

24:31.380 --> 24:33.325
Hmm.

24:33.330 --> 24:34.376
[knock on door]

24:39.460 --> 24:42.577
I found these two at the bar
causmg all sorts of trouble.

24:42.580 --> 24:45.413
Hello,
we've never met.

24:45.420 --> 24:46.455
I'm Helen.

24:46.460 --> 24:47.745
She is Hunter.

24:49.420 --> 24:51.490
Levi. On Land?

24:51.500 --> 24:53.320
[Helen] I don't know.

24:53.330 --> 24:55.321
It's mating season.
They're desperate.

24:55.330 --> 24:56.456
Oh. That explains
why I caught 'em

24:56.460 --> 24:57.745
busting a move
on some drunk dude.

24:57.750 --> 25:00.662
There's new one, a male.
Ryn brought him.

25:00.670 --> 25:02.535
-[soft hiss]
-They're up at the cabin.

25:02.540 --> 25:03.746
He's here to mate.

25:03.750 --> 25:06.492
Maybe I should just
take 'em there.

25:06.500 --> 25:09.492
Sure. Maybe you two can get
a piece of the action.

25:11.330 --> 25:13.378
Okay, back
to the truck, ladies.

25:14.420 --> 25:15.535
-Come on.
-[hisses]

25:15.540 --> 25:16.700
-Yeah, just--
-[He|en chuckles]

25:23.460 --> 25:24.700
Look, about the graveyard,

25:24.710 --> 25:26.450
I'm still trying
to figure out what happened,

25:26.460 --> 25:29.372
but I can't reach Nicole.

25:29.380 --> 25:31.666
I got a feeling
the military's involved.

25:32.830 --> 25:34.786
In robbing
my family's graves?

25:36.670 --> 25:37.705
In all of it.

25:46.670 --> 25:52.825
[Siren song echoing]

25:56.540 --> 25:57.700
I can't just sit here.

25:59.500 --> 26:00.535
I gotta take a walk.

26:12.540 --> 26:15.498
[doors close]

26:16.580 --> 26:17.820
[engine starts]

26:20.880 --> 26:23.872
So, what? Like, you both

26:23.880 --> 26:25.780
really want to have
babies right now, huh?

26:27.500 --> 26:29.411
Need babies.

26:29.420 --> 26:30.739
Why?

26:30.750 --> 26:31.785
[Eliza] No babies.

26:33.880 --> 26:35.416
What do you mean,
no babies?

26:35.420 --> 26:38.537
We try, does not happen.

26:41.500 --> 26:42.876
Oh.

26:42.880 --> 26:46.873
You mean, like,
no babies for anyone.

26:50.500 --> 26:51.535
Wow.

26:51.540 --> 26:53.496
Yes. Wow.

26:56.670 --> 26:58.570
Is finished.

26:58.580 --> 26:59.569
Oh.

27:00.580 --> 27:01.820
-Good.
-He sleeps.

27:01.830 --> 27:03.570
They usually do.

27:05.460 --> 27:06.449
Where's Ben?

27:06.460 --> 27:08.530
He went for a walk.

27:08.540 --> 27:09.700
He is angry?

27:09.710 --> 27:10.779
With me?

27:10.790 --> 27:12.872
Seems like
you're angry at him.

27:13.920 --> 27:15.615
He lie to me.

27:15.620 --> 27:17.781
He should tell me
about his family.

27:17.790 --> 27:19.610
He was afraid
of losing you.

27:23.620 --> 27:24.780
You know my mother, Susan?

27:24.790 --> 27:25.779
Yes.

27:25.790 --> 27:27.917
Remember I told you
how she was?

27:27.920 --> 27:29.820
The pain she caused me?

27:29.830 --> 27:35.575
Yes.
She was weak and sad.

27:35.580 --> 27:36.786
Am I like her?

27:38.750 --> 27:41.662
No, you are strong.

27:43.830 --> 27:46.663
Just because your family
thinks or acts a certain way

27:46.670 --> 27:48.570
doesn't mean you have
to repeat that.

27:48.580 --> 27:50.821
Ben's ashamed
of what his family did.

27:50.830 --> 27:53.492
And many in your colony
don't trust humans.

27:53.500 --> 27:54.660
They want to fight them.

27:54.670 --> 27:56.740
But you came on land,
you trusted us,

27:56.750 --> 27:58.570
fell in love with us.

28:00.580 --> 28:03.572
Love can be good
or bad.

28:04.830 --> 28:07.822
Yeah. But I trust Ben.

28:07.830 --> 28:09.536
I trust you.

28:10.790 --> 28:12.917
I trust_
that our love IS good.

28:17.920 --> 28:20.992
[soft music]

28:26.960 --> 28:29.667
[Helen] "It's hard
to put this in words.

28:29.670 --> 28:32.662
Your husband Caleb's
bizarre behavior

28:32.670 --> 28:37.869
is a constant source of fear
for me and my husband,

28:37.880 --> 28:39.780
especially
with a baby coming.

28:39.790 --> 28:41.826
He knocked me to the ground,

28:41.830 --> 28:43.957
and I'm six months pregnant."

28:43.960 --> 28:45.951
[woman screams]

28:45.960 --> 28:47.916
[Helen]
"The events of that night

28:47.920 --> 28:51.037
clearly exposed his psychosis."

28:51.040 --> 28:53.577
-[woman screams]
-"His jealousy."

28:53.580 --> 28:54.911
[screaming]

28:54.920 --> 28:57.992
"His obsession, his rage."

28:58.000 --> 29:01.572
[dramatic music]

29:01.580 --> 29:02.569
Ryn!

29:04.670 --> 29:05.739
Ryn!

29:11.580 --> 29:12.877
[groans]

29:18.580 --> 29:19.615
[bell rings]

29:24.670 --> 29:25.819
[sighs]

29:27.920 --> 29:30.912
Please, stay in the truck.

29:34.040 --> 29:35.610
[door bell jingles]

29:35.620 --> 29:37.952
[pop music playing
in market]

29:47.790 --> 29:51.954
[female singer] Just get up,
get out, and get goin'

29:51.960 --> 29:53.666
[hard rock playing in van]

29:53.670 --> 29:55.991
For the king of the jungle

29:56.000 --> 29:58.878
The nights are...

30:00.080 --> 30:02.878
-[man] Get me chips!
-Yeah, relax, drummer boy.

30:20.000 --> 30:21.069
[hisses]

30:21.080 --> 30:22.786
[soft laugh]

30:22.790 --> 30:25.748
Didn't we meet
a while back?

30:25.750 --> 30:27.069
Somewhere?

30:27.080 --> 30:28.991
Chat maybe?

30:30.000 --> 30:31.661
Here.

30:31.670 --> 30:34.662
My band has a gig
in Bristol Cove.

30:34.670 --> 30:36.911
Come check us out.
I'll buy you a drink.

30:43.830 --> 30:45.036
[hisses]

30:46.710 --> 30:48.826
Looks like
Chewey's got game.

30:51.000 --> 30:54.037
Maybe tonight
we can dance to the dawn

30:54.040 --> 30:57.874
Hands in the air,
oh, baby, come on

30:57.880 --> 31:00.952
There's nothin'
but moonlight, you, and me

31:00.960 --> 31:02.746
[cash register clicking]

31:02.750 --> 31:04.820
Oh, can you picture
my fantasy

31:04.830 --> 31:08.118
Maybe tonight
we can dance to the dawn

31:08.120 --> 31:10.953
[hard rock music in van]

31:10.960 --> 31:12.825
[inhaling]

31:17.120 --> 31:18.701
You want some?

31:18.710 --> 31:19.699
[hisses]

31:19.710 --> 31:21.780
[coughing]

31:23.120 --> 31:25.953
Yep, that's me.

31:25.960 --> 31:28.030
From water?

31:28.040 --> 31:30.747
No, I'm a city kid.

31:30.750 --> 31:32.786
'Cause now is my time

31:32.790 --> 31:33.825
Now is my time

31:33.830 --> 31:35.741
Are you doing that?

31:35.750 --> 31:37.035
-[hisses]
-Aah! Aah!

31:37.040 --> 31:40.203
Hey, man,
I'll get 40 on the...

31:41.920 --> 31:43.820
Oh, shit.

31:43.830 --> 31:44.956
What the hell?

31:45.960 --> 31:47.916
In. [hisses]

31:47.920 --> 31:49.911
[Chewey choking]

31:51.040 --> 31:53.167
[hisses] Now!

31:53.170 --> 31:55.786
[Chewey, gasping]
What just happened?

31:55.790 --> 31:57.872
You just dodged a bullet.

31:57.880 --> 32:00.781
[groaning]

32:04.210 --> 32:09.739
[Siren song echoing]

32:14.880 --> 32:17.872
[Ryn's voice]
This man in your family.

32:17.880 --> 32:20.075
[song continuing]

32:20.080 --> 32:21.911
His love turned bad.

32:24.120 --> 32:26.031
It makes him angry.

32:31.960 --> 32:33.075
Noo!

32:34.120 --> 32:35.109
Aah!

32:36.830 --> 32:38.115
No!Noo!

32:39.170 --> 32:41.240
[Ryn gasping]

32:44.250 --> 32:45.239
No.

32:47.120 --> 32:48.781
No.

32:48.790 --> 32:50.781
[gasping]

32:54.120 --> 32:56.247
[crying]

33:06.250 --> 33:07.990
[rock thuds on ground]

33:08.000 --> 33:10.070
[ominous music]

33:25.170 --> 33:26.876
You are okay?

33:30.000 --> 33:33.072
No. Not okay.

33:33.080 --> 33:34.160
Angry with me?

33:35.210 --> 33:37.246
Confused about myself.

33:37.250 --> 33:39.536
Ben,

33:39.540 --> 33:41.610
I know you
would not hurt me.

33:43.330 --> 33:45.491
I know you are different
than your family.

33:45.500 --> 33:46.489
Those who kill.

33:46.500 --> 33:48.377
I want to believe that.

33:49.380 --> 33:50.369
I believe.

33:51.620 --> 33:53.497
Our love is good.

33:56.580 --> 33:58.320
You trust me?

34:00.540 --> 34:02.667
I don't want you
to feel any more pain.

34:31.750 --> 34:34.537
[engine stops]

34:39.620 --> 34:41.417
Happy middle of the night.

34:42.540 --> 34:43.575
It's a long story.

34:51.460 --> 34:52.575
[door unlatches]

34:55.710 --> 34:58.417
Levi? Where?

34:58.420 --> 35:00.285
I don't know.

35:00.290 --> 35:01.416
With him now.

35:11.750 --> 35:12.739
-[hisses]
-[hisses]

35:14.420 --> 35:15.489
Different on land.

35:16.670 --> 35:17.785
No fight.

35:20.330 --> 35:21.376
EquaL

35:23.670 --> 35:24.659
I show you.

35:37.750 --> 35:40.492
So I guess we just--

35:40.500 --> 35:42.661
Yeah. Let them do
what they do.

35:44.750 --> 35:47.321
I'll make sure
they're comfortable.

35:56.790 --> 35:58.451
Yeah.

36:03.620 --> 36:04.609
You okay?

36:05.620 --> 36:07.451
I'm--

36:07.460 --> 36:08.609
I'm just worried

36:08.620 --> 36:09.746
about Nicole.

36:09.750 --> 36:11.490
I been trying
to reach her,

36:11.500 --> 36:13.616
but there's just nothing,
just crickets.

36:17.540 --> 36:18.609
[Ben] You stay
out here and lay low.

36:18.620 --> 36:20.576
I'll get in there.

36:20.580 --> 36:22.741
Think she pulled
an all-nighter?

36:22.750 --> 36:24.615
She would've texted.

36:26.790 --> 36:28.371
I'll find her.

36:29.670 --> 36:31.661
Okay. Be careful.

36:35.830 --> 36:39.493
[suspenseful music]

36:53.830 --> 36:56.572
[Beth] "We have lost him
in the prime of his life,

36:56.580 --> 36:58.457
and it kills me to know
that he'll never meet

36:58.460 --> 37:00.451
our beautiful baby girl."

37:01.580 --> 37:03.457
That's you
she's writing about.

37:08.750 --> 37:09.785
I, um...

37:11.790 --> 37:16.454
I may have been wrong
to blame your people
for the fire.

37:16.460 --> 37:20.783
Yes, it certainly reads
like Caleb Pownall started it.

37:20.790 --> 37:21.870
I don't know.

37:21.880 --> 37:23.609
I may never know.

37:24.880 --> 37:27.667
It was all
before we were born, Helen.

37:27.670 --> 37:28.819
Thank you for sharing this,

37:28.830 --> 37:32.573
and for your apology.

37:32.580 --> 37:34.616
That's not
the only reason I came.

37:35.880 --> 37:37.871
I also came to warn you.

38:32.750 --> 38:33.910
[scanner beeps]

38:49.580 --> 38:50.569
[beeps]

39:03.790 --> 39:06.611
[Kyle conversing]

39:06.620 --> 39:09.669
[suspenseful music]

39:21.000 --> 39:24.663
[disturbing music]

40:01.750 --> 40:05.072
[Helen] My family
has had a burial plot

40:05.080 --> 40:08.959
on a coastal hillside
in Bristol Cove.

40:08.960 --> 40:11.997
I believe the military
raided that graveyard.

40:12.000 --> 40:13.615
Oh, my dear.

40:14.710 --> 40:15.825
Oh, I'm so sorry.

40:15.830 --> 40:17.661
You don't understand, Beth.

40:17.670 --> 40:20.787
That is our family.

40:20.790 --> 40:23.076
If they analyze those bones,

40:25.620 --> 40:26.746
they'll know about us.

40:28.710 --> 40:29.950
They could find us.

40:35.750 --> 40:38.662
[cartoon soundtrack
playing in background]

40:47.790 --> 40:49.667
[man chuckling]

40:56.040 --> 40:58.076
[playing trombone]

40:59.670 --> 41:02.912
[suspenseful music]

41:11.750 --> 41:12.819
Chris?

41:15.000 --> 41:16.661
Chris.

41:18.460 --> 41:19.825
Do I, uh...

41:21.120 --> 41:22.701
Do I know you?

41:22.710 --> 41:25.110
[ominous music]

41:31.960 --> 41:34.110
[high-pitched call]

41:37.120 --> 41:40.783
[music playing]
